.TH "intel_uncore_forcewake_for_reg" 9 "intel_uncore_forcewake_for_reg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_uncore_forcewake_for_reg \- which forcewake domains are needed to access a register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "enum forcewake_domains" intel_uncore_forcewake_for_reg
.BI "(struct intel_uncore *uncore "  ","
.BI "i915_reg_t reg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int op "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "uncore" 12
pointer to struct intel_uncore
.IP "reg" 12
register in question
.IP "op" 12
operation bitmask of FW_REG_READ and/or FW_REG_WRITE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns a set of forcewake domains required to be taken with for example
intel_uncore_forcewake_get for the specified register to be accessible in the
specified mode (read, write or read/write) with raw mmio accessors.
.SH "NOTE"
On Gen6 and Gen7 write forcewake domain (FORCEWAKE_RENDER) requires the
callers to do FIFO management on their own or risk losing writes.
